fields.name: Chicago Marathon Cheers
fields.description: On Sunday morning, Oct. 12, UIC students and other members of the UIC community gathered along Halsted and Taylor streets to cheer on the thousands of runners striving and sweating to finish the Chicago Marathon. The 26-mile course passed through campus at mile 17.5, at the official UIC Cheer Zone, just after the challenging uphill I-290 overpass.

fields.name: Movie Under the Stars
fields.description: September 18th, on University Hall Lawn, the Student Activities Board hosted a free screening of Scream(1986) for the UIC community. Free popcorn and smores provided!
